reviews.title: Reservation and not having a place
reviews.text:
A few weeks ago reserved for 6 people on August 1 at 6 pm called that we arrived half an hour later was no problem.
When we report offer at 6.30 there was no place for us. We had to take a drink outside and wait for space to open up. How can this be?? 
We went to another eatery where space was made.

reviews.title: Delicious!
reviews.text: Very good food! Good and spacious portions. Nachos as an appetizer also really super tasty. Service was completely good for us, time between courses not too short and not too long. I'd eat there again.

reviews.title: Great restaurant
reviews.text:
It was warm and very busy, but helped quickly and friendly. Staff is top! In that warmth and hustle so efficient and friendly to operate, hats off.
Food and drink also came quickly and was just good and lots.
Here you can eat really good for normal price

reviews.title: Great Mexican food.
reviews.text: Service is great. They don't keep you waiting long. The food is very delicious. If you have any wishes regarding food they will serve you the best way they can. The staff will give you a feeling you are much appreciated at every visit. 5***** a real recommendation.

reviews.title: Not Tex Mex like in Texas
reviews.text: Look this is Holland not SW USA so don't expect lots of spicy dish's with Extra large portions. Eg Nacho Grandad comes on a small dinner plate with two dozen chips 2 tiny pieces of jalapeno no salsa no guacamole. Having said that we were very surprised how tasty it was with beautiful Dutch cheese, just wish we would have ordered two. Our dishes were all served nicely and were tasty inspite being totally devoid of spice in fact on the spicy scale I would consider all of the  dishes we sampled would be mild by North American standards. I would hazard to guess that if a highly rated Tex Mex restaurant opened in Holland it wouldn't work due to the difference in tastes. So to some up it was good food good service just don't expect authentic Tex Mex.

reviews.title: Busy place with friendly staff
reviews.text: Had dinner here with the family and grand parents, made a reservation but table given away as reservations are unusual so arrive early. Place was very busy but staff had a smile on their face. Classic mexican menu and spme choice for the kids too. Value for money.

reviews.title: Birthday dinner
reviews.text: Great restaurant. We were with a group of 10 and even though we didn't make a reservation the created room for us. The food, which was a mixture of several dishes, was delicious and the waiters very friendly

reviews.title: Texmex in nice ambience
reviews.text: Food is comparable with most texmex restaurants. Price/quality good. Nice Mexican food in a cosy atmosphere.

reviews.title: Excellent texmex
reviews.text: Beautiful spot in old borne. Food is comparable with most texmex restaurants in the states. Price/quality good. Just, nice Mexican food. One of the better restaurants in the neighbourhood.

reviews.title: Cosy family restaurant with great mexican dishes
reviews.text:
Las Carretas is a nice family restaurant in the center of borne. They serve nice affordable mexican dishes.
They also have a nice terrace for a sunny evening or afternoon.
